### EntryRequest Cancel Update Examples

### 1. Actualizar EntryRequest con cancelación completa
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO",
  "idCancelReason": 1,
  "cancelReason": "Cliente canceló el pedido",
  "idCancelDetail": 2,
  "cancelDetail": "Cambio de fecha de cirugía"
}

### 2. Actualizar solo el status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO"
}

### 3. Actualizar con razón de cancelación
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO",
  "idCancelReason": 3,
  "cancelReason": "Equipo no disponible"
}

### 4. Actualizar con detalle de cancelación
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO",
  "idCancelDetail": 1,
  "cancelDetail": "Paciente no asistió a la cita"
}

### 5. Error: Sin companyCode
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO",
  "cancelReason": "Error de prueba"
}

### 6. Error: EntryRequest inexistente
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/999999/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELADO",
  "cancelReason": "EntryRequest que no existe"
}

### 7. Actualizar con valores nulos
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/EntryRequest/123/cancel?companyCode=COMP001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ACTIVO",
  "idCancelReason": null,
  "cancelReason": null,
  "idCancelDetail": null,
  "cancelDetail": null
}

### Variables para Postman/VS Code REST Client
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@companyCode = COMP001
@entryRequestId = 123
